div.font: Like with so many people, Lennon has had one really bad experience with a subscription: One of Lennon's hobbies to get away from work is art. In the past they created many paintings they would sell at the farmers market. At one point Lennon got his hands on a free trial for Adobe Photoshop which features digital painting. He thought he would give it a try for a week. Several weeks go by with Lennon being busy at work but he finally gets around to canceling the subscription. To his horror however, his free trial had ended, automatically becoming a paid account 15 days ago, which meant in order to cancel he had to pay 50% of the annual cost which is over $100. This experience was a huge let down that made his hobby he had once used to get away from stress a stressful experience itself. Had he known how dangerous it was to get a free trial from Adobe he would have gladly of never used their software.
